ts of music. He has particular Indian friends that he performs with and so on. He also composes. And they told me, when he graduated \endash  by which time, his father had died \endash 
 that he could either be a composer, a musicologist, or an executant, he was he was first class all round. He is married with two children, although his wife has just parted, but I think they\rquote re better off. She\rquote 
s gone off with a woman, and I think they remain good friends, and she\rquote s not living far away. And her partner is a wonderful woman, so that\rquote s good. Peter works largely from home, but he\rquote 
s bombing all over the place all the time, and he teaches world music in the Carmarthenshire schools on a part-time basis. Because he never got maths at GCSE, he can\rquote t get a full-time teaching job, even now. Crazy! And he\rquote 
s proven as a good teacher. But, never mind. 
