\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid9241263 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 Plus there was this big difference - I don\rquote 
t think that sociology had formally declared itself a profession 
by the time that second study started, but there was a whole professionalising thing had been going on in the interval, and whereas, really I was very much a lone person working in that kind of area, there was a lot more people writing books about how one
 ought to do research. I never thought of myself as a methodologist, but finally I was persuaded to write a book on the methods of social research, which I did one long vacation, in six weeks flat, and I\rquote ve never understood why I couldn\rquote 
