\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 
Now, one of the things that is quite important, I think, about the Banbury Study, is the way that you do try to use both the survey and participant observation. Do you feel that that worked, combining qualitative and quantitative data?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 Meg:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 I\rquote m not quite sure what it would mean, \'93that it worked\'94
, but I think that they were complementary to each other. I mean, if you\rquote re trying to make a statement about a place like that, when you can\rquote t possibly kn
ow everybody, or interview everybody, there is some need to understand the frequency with which people like that speak, in terms of the people you\rquote 
ve talked to, actually turn up on the scene. And one of the only ways of doing that is to have some sort of basic survey data of the age and marital status and all of those boring things. So I think those two methods, go together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\insrsid544046\charrsid1901768 Fine. Do you think there\rquote s anything more to say about the Banbury Study, that you want to say?

